caption: Great beer, safe and clean environment with COVID, great cabanas when its cold and a huge outdoor patio! Dog friendly and yummy food too!
Fresh, modern decor with great beers. I am a big fan of Belgian and sour styles and their selection is some of the best in the city.
Great staff, following covid guidelines and taking all precautions, great infrastructure, and great beers on rotation. If you’re a beer lover, you’ll know what this place is about.

Chill vibes with a strong mix of local incubator breweries, modern ambiance, and unique takes on bar food favorites are what set Pilot Project apart.  I was personally happy with the great variety of beers at the time we visited, though I understand there's some fluidity to being an incubator. The pretzel and beer cheese was a standout item - betrer for groups of 3+and the BBQ chicken sandwich was great.  We sat indoors - a mix of couches and high tops, though there was semi-permenant facilities outside which were considerably more impressive than the shanties set up by peer restaurants and beers.  I will visit here again for sure.
Great service and an excellent selection of beers (including great sours)!
Great coffee, great beer, great neighbors
It's 5F outside, please get some heaters! It's the bare minimum I would expect from any hospitality establishment. Pathetic infrastructure
Super cool spot with great vibes! Their beer and cider is each unique with delicious flavors. You can reserve a spot in their heated cabanas and try a flight.

Decent beer. $10 to reserve cabana which is understandable during the pandemic but they’re still around 50 F degrees. The CTA blue runs every 5-10 minutes behind you and it’s very loud. Not their fault
Wonderful independent brewery.
Great spot to chill and taste some experimental beer!
Great place to taste experimental beers.  Cool outdoor space and friendly staff.

Lovely beers, lovely staff, wonderful with Covid-19 safety restrictions! You can reserve a table on the patio ahead of time, which is great so you don't have to wait for a table. Masks required for any interactions with the staff and outside your table. Tables are well spaced. Everything is nice and clean. Love this spot!

Big patio built on top of a parking lot.  L is right next to the patio and very loud so not very enjoyable unfortunately.  Inside is very nice.  Beers are 1-2 bucks pricer than other comparable breweries.  Great spot to work from during the day.
The perfect pup friendly brewery! We love it here. Great beer and awesome staff

Modern & open interior with lots of outdoor seating. Perfect for either working/studying/reading or hanging out with a group of friends. I had a flight of different beers and am a fan of the brewery’s style. Also great for taking pictures with the sleek and artsy interior as a background
I'll definitely be coming back! Too many good beers to choose from is always a good problem to have.
Great spot to do some work with a brew or cool off with a brew. Staff keeping everyone safe with strict protocols
Amazing food and beer with lots of variety. Great patio space, great service, and I felt very comfortable in the space. Highly recommend.
Beautiful ambiance
Great space.   We tried 3 beers and really enjoyed all of them.   Good sours and saison.   Felt covid safe in big outdoor space.

A nearby spot for us and we love Pilot. Amazing assortment of unique beers that you likely will not find anywhere else in the city. The space is beautiful and open, you’ll often find people there solo enjoying a coffee or beer while they get some work done.  Pilot also has a large outdoor area full of picnic tables and dog friendly :)
Try the orange mountains only. It's incredible
Great atmosphere,  delicious beers,  good service, couldn't ask for more. the patio ita very cool,  love the view of the Congress theater.

Great beers with a good selection, but more importantly: they actually act like there is a pandemic happening! It has truly been tough to find places that are respecting guidelines (quickly checking temps as you enter, masks on when talking to waiters, and properly spaced out tables). If you want to support a local spot, get a beer with some buds, and not potentially harm others -- this is your place!
Delicious beers, friendly staff! This is my new favorite spot. They have a wide variety of beers, something for everyone!
Sandwiches are simple but very good. Great selection of sours.

Pilot Project has such a great variety of beers, wonderful staff and awesome atmosphere. The outdoor patio is first come first serve. They have a good, safe setup for enjoying outdoor beers with friends. Street parking on Milwaukee is pay to park, neighborhood parking is bit challenging because it’s mostly are zoned streets. Definitely give Pilot Project a visit!
Great selection, laid back environment. Nice patio. Love how many sour beers they have.
Always a great spot on their patio or inside. They have a great beverage selection that will satisfy any palate!
Plenty of space to work or socialize. Quick service at the counter. Plenty of coffee, tea, beer and cider choices. Meat and cheese plates and sandwiches to feed you. Great spot!
Really good selection

This cafe / brewery in Logan square is beautiful, spacious, and filled with everything I love - strong espresso, decent WiFi, beer and wine and everything in between, and floor to ceiling windows filling the room with natural light. I came here to get some work done on a Sunday, will definitely be back to check out the vibe during the week. Would recommend!
Great selections. I will be back.

Great spot for working, a business meeting, catching up with a friend or just lounging. They offer a good selection of coffees, beers and kombucha. The staff is very friendly, the atmosphere is quaint and the interior is modern and vibrant. The music is chill and volume level is perfect. I ordered the Rose Latte and really enjoyed it. Overall a great experience, would definitely come back.

So glad we stumbled upon this place this past weekend while looking for a bar. The space is beautiful, multi-functional, and feels very chic and millennial. It's extremely spacious and perfect for grabbing a casual drink with friends in the evening, or for pulling out a laptop to work during the day.  The concept is so unique. Essentially, Pilot Project is a beer incubator and produces small batch brews of very interesting drinks, including hard kombucha (my fave) and CBD cider. We got a couple beers and kombuchas in half pours and tasters, but there are also options to get them in larger or smaller pours. I'll definitely be back during the day to enjoy the space!

Such a unique and fun venue! The staff was extremely nice and friendly. I loved the variety of unique drinks they offered. Kombucha, beer wine mixes, and cheese platters. So good. Please check this place out if you’re in the area!
Nice, clean, lively yet quiet place to get some work done.
Great interior, great beer selection
Great meeting place and spot to try new brews.
Love the beer, the space, the staff and the patio!
Great beer and atmosphere.  Love the Kombucha option.  Would recommend for large groups.
Wonderful new brewery that has top notch beer and cider along with a great indoor and outdoor space. The patio is dog friendly and the staff is the best. We will certainly be back
I love the concept and the space is welcoming & has a great aesthetic. The variety of local brews, coffee and food is an added bonus. I’ll definitely be back!
Love that I can also get hard cider and kombucha. Porch is spacious but a little noisy with the Blue Line going by. Great decor and ambiance inside. Mostly younger crowd.
Such an amazingly place!  Beer is great.  Atmosphere is awesome as well!  I will for sure be back!  Check it out.
Good brewery. Sat on patio to have a few beers
Loved the blueberry cider and the grilled cheese!!
Very interesting new concept. Trendy coffee house vibe for brewery. Large waffle selection and great looking coffee, I didn't have any... House beers are solid!

Really beautiful space with plenty of tables and seating. During the day the music is very soft so it's productive for working. Amazing coffee, kombucha, and assorted small bites to eat including pastries and charcuterie. Haven't had a chance to check it out in the afternoon but looking forward to it.

Adult tested. Dog approved.  Marked this down on my list as my new favorite Neighborhood brewery. (Tied with Maplewood!)  There's an outside patio for pooches and people. The inside is roomy with tasteful decorations and comfy looking couches.  What drew me to this brewery was the range of beer, ciders, and kombucha. I want to try everything. I'll be a regular here before I know it.  I ordered a flight with lavender kombucha, blueberry kombucha,  Mr Sparkles (farmhouse ale), and the red cider. Mr Sparkles was my least favorite due to a malty flavor. I was expecting more lemon. I also tried the Mexican lager, which was smooth and creamy. I'm a fan.  I can't wait to try the rest of the menu, not to mention the food menu. Nice addition to the neighborhood!

Beer was great, but unfortunately i had some issues with the bar itself which is stopping me from giving a solid 4/5. I felt the lights were a bit too bright in the bar, at least for the aesthetic the brewery was going for. And for whatever unknown reason they started blasting some unpleasing emo music which totally killed the vibe and my friends and I promptly left. I would love to give this place a second chance but I am not interested in hearing some terrible music while I am trying to relax and do work.
Any place that supports local brewing gets a 5 from me.
10/10 would go again
Like an apple store, but without the warm atmosphere and friendly clientele.

I absolutely love this place. The decor and overall vibe is amazing. Adding coffee during the day was a great idea. I am a full time student and this will be a great spot to study during the day, but also a spot to relax with friends over some beer in the evening. Thank you for this wonderful edition to Logan Square!
Another establishment overrun by laptops. Shame. Stunning place great beers, just not my crowd.
Cool place. Beer's good, too 🍺😉
Calm space, great staff and tasty beers. Lots of great starts for this brewery thay now has a brewery tap room as of a weeks ago. Congratulations!!
Open and inviting space. Fantastic staff, especially Jordan! Delicious house beers are brewed on site. Will definitely return to try their Kombucha.
Big space with both indoor and outdoor seats. The beer is different but good. The waffle is mind blowing and delicious

A spot for everyone! Big for beer drinkers, but approachable for those who don’t love beer. The hard Booch is great. The decor is outstanding. Such a fun hangout in the mornings with coffee, especially to work. This place dazzles.
Great new spot with great beer and great coffee.  I spent the day working there yesterday and it was fantastic.  I will be back!
Had a great time piloting a flight with my wife on the patio.  Going to stop in soon for a coffee beverage.  Great ambiance
Great beer, the place is really awesome! My favorite was the mañana de Mallorca :)
